    "Specifically, DL algorithms possess intrinsic regularization features within their back propagation learning process.",
    "Intriguingly, these features can actually reduce the risk of overfitting as the network scales -contrary to what one might expect, adding more nodes or layers can make the model more robust.",
    "This upends our traditional understanding from classical statistics and ML, where increased model complexity usually exacerbates overfitting.",
